      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/synthesis-prior-studies-hemolysis",
      "type": "uofa:Evidence",
      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modelling studies",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior experimental and computational studies on pump-induced hemolysis, including the Goubergrits & Affeld (2004) power-law damage model calibration, the Giersiepen et al. (1990) empirical correlation for erythrocyte destruction, and the FDA Critical Path initiative benchmark results (2011–2017). This synthesis was assembled by the V&V team as a consolidated reference document integrating published NIH thresholds, validated turbulence model selections for blood pump CFD, and accepted scalar stress proxy formulations. It serves as the methodological foundation for model form and input parameter selections in this assessment.",
      "uofa:evidenceType": "LiteratureSynthesis",
      "uofa:sourceDocuments": [
        "https://doi.org/10.1097/00004872-200407001-00004",
